underlying_goal: The user wanted to fix a `ValueError` in the prompt selection pipeline caused by inhomogeneous embedding shapes.
primary_success: Claude correctly diagnosed that the cache was polluted with mock embeddings of the wrong dimension from previous dry runs, and implemented a robust fix.
brief_summary: A script was failing with a `ValueError` due to inconsistent array shapes. Claude diagnosed that the cache was polluted with a mix of real 1536-dimension embeddings and mock 256-dimension embeddings from dry runs. Claude fixed the issue by adding dimension validation to the cache loading logic and correcting the mock data dimension to prevent future issues.
